commitmsg: Moved passwords-don't-match error to password2 field.
Fixed bug in core API layer.
new home products page has no crumb
Fixed breadcrumb link in test pages.
Removed Add Test Case nav item if you're not logged in.
Moved product list to home page.
Moved user-creation inside RegistrationForm in preparation for making username/email conflicts show up as form validation errors.
Updated User.setroles() and Role.setpermissions() to not blank out the User/Role by trying to update from the response.
Updated RemoteObject to clear out any URL override in favor of resourceIdentity URL when an object is fetched.
Updated setpermissions and setroles to pass originalVersionId.
Use object auth when fetching related Locator field values.
Extended credentials-passing in and out of List objects.
Switched to application/json content-type for PUTting to users/login and users/logout.
Added content-type header to DELETE requests now that API support it.
Default to cached list-object auth for posting a new object to that list.
Moved login and logout methods to User.
Added kwargs to RemoteObject get, put, post methods, to allow passing in auth.
Added more explicit authentication for requests.
Added user activation/deactivation, email change and confirmation, password change to API access layer.
Removed content-type from DELETE requests, hopefully pending API fix to allow it.
Moved StaticData field into static/ to avoid circular dependencies.
Upgraded to django-compressor 0.6a8 (with cache backend fix for 1.3).
Modified bin/install-reqs to call pip in-process.
Switched to non-ssh url for requirements submodule.
Added username field to registration form wireframe.
Switched to urlparse.parse_qs; cgi.parse_qs is deprecated.
Added StaticField and unicode decoding of response.
Added ResourceIdentity; split fields into separate module.
Cleaned up; moved prefix-stripping and nil-interpretation to Field class.
smoke tests are now working against qa test server.  many other tests fail, however
But we need the equivalent of readline -f.
Added initial requirements file and pip install script.
added version of the mock .war file.  Also some updates to tests
adding a little readme with simple setup steps
Fix case of Ids submission parameter for PUTting to a List.
Added environment-filtering on test cycle and test run list pages.
breaking steps into separate object centered modules.  new smoke tests.
Added match() method to EnvironmentGroup and EnvironmentGroupList.
Updated versionincrement method, still not working.
Don't submit fields that aren't directly modifiable anyway.
Fixed Tag queries and removed CompanyLinkedRemoteObject.
Added TestCaseAssignment and TestResult resource models.
Fields don't work if defined on classes that aren't RemoteObjects.
Added support for just assigning a list to a Link field that links to a SomethingList.
Fixed sort UI for startDate and endDate columns.
Made sort UI styles dynamic on test cycles list.
fixed product list and table bugs
Added sort functionality to test-cycles list.
Avoid recursive access of request.user in case of invalid user data in session.
Use correct auth in cycles view, now that API permissions are fixed.
Store individual environment IDs in session to be more robust against odd environment group configurations.
Environment selection forms respect previous selection.
Summarize current environment in submeta, if set.
Added a bit of security-consciousness to resolve_url.
Reworked unwrap_template_syntax_errors decorator to not crash if there's no wrapped exception, and to be applicable using @decorator syntax.
environment on all test pages, wireframed
Moved environments dropdown (still needs styling and dynamic).
Rename utility object_or_id method, add some docstrings.
Added .ours() shortcut to lists for convenient narrowing to TCM_COMPANY_ID.
If newly POSTed object has no auth set, use auth from list resource it was POSTed to.
Allow request with no self._location if explicit URL is provided.
Use parent object auth if needed when setting Link attribute.
Display whether an environment type is a group type or not.
Added proper permission check for showing Add Test Case nav item.
Support for PUT to lists of linked objects.
Support to_dict() for objects without version.
Allowed self.auth to override passed-in auth=None.
added tests for testcases and products.  did some refactoring to split steps out to object type specific steps.
Improved Field.submit_data so subclasses can just define .encode() and return a dictionary with multiple values if needed.
Added environment links, Locator support for forward-refs.
Switched to generic and more informative __unicode__ representation for models.
most of the smoketests are now passing.  much refactoring.
Reworked auth decorators to catch Forbidden/Unauthorized directly from the API and redirect to login.
Fixed activate/deactivate methods to update from response again.
Fixed RemoteObject handling of zero-length lists.
Increased flexibility of RemoteObject._request() and updated RemoteObject.post() accordingly.
Added IPython shell profile for more convenient shell debugging.
Updated error-parsing for fixed JSON output from API.
Refactored request methods, added Role.addpermission and Role.removepermission.
Added user activation and default role on registration, preventing login of inactive/disabled users.
Updated registration-form error checking to use error keys, not grep text error message.
Added graceful handling of email / username conflicts on registration.
Added support for 409 Conflict, and refactored API error handling.
